metadata.symbol: Your source for blockchain first editions of classic works of literature.
metadata.description:
Lewis Carroll's Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (often reduced to Alice in Wonderland) is one of the most well-known works of literature around the world. Originally printed in 1865, after only 2000 copies had been printed illustrator John Tenniel requested a reprint due to the poor picture quality of the illustrations. While most of those original first editions were recalled, Carroll had given away a few copies to families and friends. Today, there are only 23 known copies of the original first edition in print. One of these first editions has been valued at between $2,000,000-$3,000,000.

This NFT brings the original text and original artwork to the blockchain for the first time. While priority has been given to the original text and illustrations without elaborate formatting decisions, the original shape and placement of the illustrations has been maintained as well as careful attention to font. In order preserve the value of this masterpiece for a new generation of collectors, there have only been 10 copies minted.Â
